observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management direct all personnel concerned to:
Cancel the executed importation letter of credit with a foreign supplier;
Refrain from entering a similar kind of transaction in the future;
Effect payment only to the contracted and rightful supplier; and
Follow strictly the provisions of RA 9184 regarding the payment using the letter of credit.

We recommended Management, upon determination of the necessary data, to:
Direct the Municipal Accountant to transfer in the books of accounts of LGU the fully completed infrastructure projects from the CIP account to appropriate Infrastructure Asset;
Subsequently, recognize and maintain the appropriate depreciation of the reclassified Infrastructure.

We recommended Management to ensure proper recording of financial transactions by requiring the: 

MEE Administrator to-

furnish the Municipal Accountant’s Office, copies of the previous and current notarized contract of lease of stallholders; 

Municipal Accountant to-

prepare appropriate adjusting entries to record the uncollected balances from stallholders as of December 31, 2019

ensure that the succeeding revenues from contract of lease will be recorded in accordance with accrual basis and Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards;

